programme.title: Donal Lunny - Linte Ceoil Cheiltigh
programme.desc: Donal Lunny journeys the thousand miles from the Outer Hebrides to Galicia. As he travels he records, building upon a series of carefully researched key tunes, layering and juxtaposing the traditional music of the Celtic nations. Could traditional music, that passed on orally, hold real evidence, tangible clues to a common Celtic heritage?(c)

programme.title: Never Been Kissed
programme.desc: Drew Barrymore enchants as a Chicago newspaper editor who relives her hellish teen years while on an undercover assignment at a local high school. Raja Gosnell is the director, and Barrymore served as executive producer

However, after unleashing this new phenomenon on the world, society quickly falls apart. Directed by Ricky Gervais. Jennifer Garner, Jonah Hill, Louis C.K

programme.title: Orange County
programme.desc: With the help of his stoner brother, a California scholar seeks an alternate route to Stanford when the usual college-admissions process doesn't work

programme.title: Along Came a Spider
programme.desc: After losing his partner in an out of control bust, forensic psychologist Dr. Alex Cross (Morgan Freeman) stops working and cannot forgive himself. But he¿s drawn back to work when a brilliant but remorseless psychopath who has landed a teaching position at an exclusive private school in Washington, D.C. abducts one of his students, the daughter of a senator. Ollie MacArthur, the detective investigating the case, has strong words for Jezzie Flannigan, the Secret Service agent who mistakenly let Megan slip through her fingers. But Dr. Cross seeks out Flannigan, who he believes might have a valuable insight into the case. Soon, they both come to the terrible realization that this crime only represents the tip of the iceberg for the ruthless criminal

programme.title: Dolores Claiborne
programme.desc: A big-city journalist discovers a terrible secret about her family's past after her estranged mother becomes the prime suspect in the death of the elderly woman for whom she had been caring. Soon the daughter learns the details of her father's mysterious death years before, and eventually she realizes how profoundly she misunderstood her mother

programme.title: Without a Trace
programme.desc: Kate Nelligan as a mother searching for her missing 6-year-old. Judd Hirsch, David Dukes, Stockard Channing, Jacqueline Brookes, Keith McDermott. Stanley R. Jaffe directed

programme.title: The Cider House Rules
programme.desc: An orphan grows up under the tutelage of a kindly doctor in World War II Maine, where the young man refuses to assist his mentor with the illegal abortions that he performs in hopes of keeping the women from dangerous incompetents. Michael Caine won the Best Supporting Actor Oscar as the doctor

programme.title: Class Action
programme.desc: Father and daughter lawyers (Gene Hackman, Mary Elizabeth Mastrantonio) become adversaries in a lawsuit against an auto company. Grazier: Colin Friels. Estelle: Joanna Merlin. Holbrook: Larry Fishburne. Quinn: Donald Moffat. Pavel: Jan Rubes. Brian: Jonathan Silverman. Directed by Michael Apted

programme.title: The Fugitive
programme.desc: Academy Award nominee Harrison Ford stars as the wrongly convicted Dr. Richard Kimble, and Academy Award winner Tommy Lee Jones is U.S. Marshal Sam Gerard, his relentless pursuer, in this all-time classic intense thriller based on the hit television series of the 1960s, The Fugitive. Kimble had the perfect life - a beautiful wife, medical career, an expensive townhouse - a perfect life until the night his wife was murdered, died in his arms and he was convicted of the crime. On his way to the penitentiary, Kimble escapes. Now, like hunted prey, he keeps running, determined only to find his wife's murderer. Caught in a nightmare from which he cannot awaken, Dr. Richard Kimble is the fugitive

programme.title: Fletch Lives

programme.title: Arthur
programme.desc: Playboy man-child Arthur learns that his wealthy mother will only give him his inheritance if he agrees to marry the daughter of a millionaire. However, Arthur hates his intended bride and instead falls for an unlicensed tour guide

programme.title: Do the Right Thing
programme.desc: A local black community is unhappy that their community is effectively being run by whites. As the heat rises on a hot summer's day in Brooklyn, so the racial tension, which has so far lay dormant under the surface, begins to rise

programme.title: The Postman Always Rings Twice
programme.desc: Jack Nicholson and Jessiac Lange star in Bob Rafelson's steamy re-make of the classic film noir, he the drifter who comes into her life, she the wife of a diner owner (John Colicos). They conspire to kill him so they can be together and take the diner for themselves but, despite their seeming success, fate has a final hand to play

programme.title: U.S. Marshals
programme.desc: United States Marshall Sam Gerard has been assigned to escort a federal prisoner to a maximum security prison in Missouri. On the same flight is Mark Sheridan, who has been arrested and charged with the murders of two Federal agents, though he insists he's innocent. The plane is involved in an accident leading to a crash, and after helping to rescue some of the passengers, Sheridan escapes

programme.title: The Beach
programme.desc: Danny Boyle's film stars Leonard Di Caprio as Richard, a free-spirited traveller who ends up in Bangkok. Frustrated by the sameness of the western experience in the city, he is intrigued when traveller Daffy tells him of an island paradise. Equipped with a map, and accompanied by French couple Francoise and Etienne, the trio eventually find the titular beach, a commune benevolently ruled by Sal. But as Richard finds out, the real world, in all its violent forms, has a habit of intruding on even the most perfect idyll..

programme.title: Cop Car
programme.desc: Two rebellious young boys steal a police cruiser and go for a joyride. But when they find a dead body in the trunk, they realize they must evade the car's owner, a corrupt small-town sheriff who's desperate to reclaim his property

programme.title: Fargo
programme.desc: The Coen brothers' sly drama about a policewoman (Frances McDormand) who's trying to determine how several murders and a kidnapping are linked to an unassuming car salesman (William H. Macy). Showalter: Steve Buscemi. Grimsrud: Peter Stormare

programme.title: Keeping Up With the Joneses
programme.desc: An ordinary suburban couple discover that their hospitable new neighbors are actually government spies. Soon, all four of them are caught up in an international espionage imbroglio

programme.title: The Fabulous Baker Boys
programme.desc: Piano-playing brothers, one a prodigy, the other mediocre, meet a chanteuse who livens up their act but whose affair with one may break them up

programme.title: Whip It
programme.desc: Bliss Cavendar (Ellen Page) es una joven que crece en un pequeño pueblo de Texas, entre los partidos de fútbol de su padre Earl (Daniel Stern) y los concursos de belleza de su madre (Marcia Gay Harden). Un panorama desolador. Bliss está harta de todo eso y encuentra consuelo en su amiga Pash (Alia Shawkat), quien le propone una opción para escapar de ese mundo de tristeza y entender el sentido real de la vida

programme.title: Reno 911!

With no tomorrow to worry about and plenty of time on his hands, Phil gets to explore some of his favourite fantasies, becomes an expert at all things trivial and pointless, gets lucky with the local girls and continually strikes out with the real love of his life. programme.title: Planet 51
programme.desc: Jorge Blanco's animation is as witty and family-friendly as you'd expect from a film that's written by Joe Stillman, who also wrote Shrek and Shrek 2. Astronaut Chuck Baker lands on Planet 51, expecting to plant a flag, hit a few golf balls and go home. of 1950s America, complete with a fascination with alien-invasion films. But this planet is inhabited by small, green aliens (is there any other kind?) whose society mirrors that The aliens are therefore terrified by their 'invader', just as he is by them. Only teenage astronomer Lem (Justin Long) appears unperturbed. He befriends Chuck and, in shades of ET, hides him in his home, before they embark on a journey to get Chuck back to his ship before it returns to Earth. There's plenty for kids and parents alike to enjoy in this affectionate dig at 50s society. Vocal talents include Gary Oldman, Seann William Scott, Jessica Biel and John Cleese

This powerful ring has been conceived by Sauron, the dark Lord of Mordor (Sala Baker), and with it, it is possible to enslave the whole of the Middle-earth through the use of dark forces. To destroy the ring, Frodo must take it to a distant mountain in Mordor, a region controlled by the Master of Evil. programme.desc: Matt Reeves' smart monster thriller has been favourably compared to The Blair Witch Project , with which it shares the concept of using "found" camcorder footage to reveal its horrors. The film opens at a party for Manhattan yuppie Rob Hawkins where the revelries are interrupted by a loud explosion. As he and his friends Hud, Jason, Marlena and Lily emerge onto the street, the head of the Statue of Liberty cartwheels past them. Something very big, scaly and angry is trashing the city, and one of the targets is a high-rise where Beth, Rob's girlfriend lives. The group set out in a rescue bid, with Hud recording everything as they make their way through what has become a nightmarish New York, threatened both by the monster (only ever half-glimpsed, making it even more terrifying) and the parasitic lice it sheds, which develop a taste for human flesh. Will all, or indeed any, of the group make it to safety? The footage tells their stories in shocking, handheld detail in this superbly paced movie
